Week 5: Hydrogen Diffusion and Trapping in Metals, a theoretical approach to Embrittlement

When: Friday, 4th October, 2024
Where: MP408
Time: 5pm onwards

Abstract: 
Hydrogen Embrittlement (HE) is a critical issue in industries that rely on high-strength metallic materials, such as the aerospace and energy sectors. It occurs when hydrogen atoms diffuse into a metal’s microstructure, resulting in cracks and reducing the material’s load-bearing capacity. This phenomenon is exacerbated by environmental factors like temperature, pressure, and corrosive agents, as well as manufacturing defects. While advanced alloys and protective measures have been developed to mitigate HE, the examination of its effects requires time and resources for the preparation and tensile testing of alloys. Although cathodic charging methods have been utilized to accelerate HE in samples, there is much room for failure, further extending experiment time. Therefore, theoretical models, such as those based on Fick’s laws of diffusion, play a crucial role in predicting HE under different conditions, offering a more efficient approach to study hydrogen diffusion, trapping, and embrittlement. This talk explores the mechanisms of HE, including hydrogen-enhanced localized plasticity and hydrogen-induced decohesion, and proposes a phenomenological model that simulates hydrogen diffusion and trapping. This model produces a highly accurate model of hydrogen transport and diffusion in a metal based on initial conditions confirmed by experimental evidence.

Week 4: Name that Neutrino, a Citizen Science Project 

When: Thursday, 26th Sept 2024
Where: MP408
Time: 5pm onwards 

Abstract:
Name that Neutrino is a citizen science project which aims to include science enthusiasts in neutrino research. The project employs volunteers alongside machine learning tools to classify neutrino detections. In my talk I will present the project and the work that I contributed to its next phase.

Week 3: Getting to know Solar Cells.

When: Friday, 20th Sept 2024
Where: MP408
Time: 5pm onwards 

Abstract: 
Solar cells play a crucial role in advancing the renewable energy sector. Are you familiar with any solar cell products in our daily lives? How much do you know about the functioning of solar cells? Are you curious about the challenges they face? In my talk this Friday, I will delve into these topics and introduce you to the fascinating world of solar cells.
